i did n't know what tribe i was and thus i remained seated .
the rest stood up , first the group of the hutus , then the tutsis .
our teacher was also a neighbour and she knew my tribe as she knew my father ; he asked me why i did not stand up and i asked her why i should have stood up and she asked me @: "@ do n't you know you 're tutsi ? @"
