i finally got used to it and stop feeling like being a tutsi was an issue .
i remember a conversation i had with mom while i was in primary iv .
i wanted more explanations and she then told me what exactly happened to my grandfather .
she told me how in 1959 , they came and took her dad , she was 16 and a mature person .
